import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { withBase } from '../lib/data.js';
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="Who's behind the Meditation Science Registry: a volunteer project, its stake, its funding, and its independence commitments.">
  <p class="eyebrow">Who's behind this</p>
  <h1>About the registry</h1>
  <p class="lede">The credibility of this registry rests on being honest about who builds it and why. So rather than claim to be a disinterested party, we state our stake plainly.</p>

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>The Meditation Science Registry is built and maintained by a small group of volunteers. Some of us practice and value one of the featured techniques — Miracle of Mind, the free app that delivers the Isha Kriya practice. We think being open about that is the credibility mechanism, not a liability to hide. (The Miracle of Mind app is itself publicly described as volunteer-built, so this framing is consistent with how the practice's own organization describes it.)</p>

  <h2>Why our stake doesn't bias the ratings</h2>
  <p>Having a stake and being fair are not in conflict, provided the rules are fixed in advance and applied identically. That is what we do:</p>
  <div class="prose">
    <ul>
      <li>Every featured practice uses the same page template, the same evidence hierarchy and the same six-axis scorecard.</li>
      <li>There is no scoring bonus for any tradition or affiliated institution — including ours.</li>
      <li>Miracle of Mind is rated at exactly the strength its own direct evidence supports. That evidence is currently thin: its one genuine randomized trial (of Isha Kriya, the closely similar practice it delivers) was null on its primary outcome, and we say so on <a href={withBase('/techniques/miracle-of-mind')}>its page</a>, in the same limitations language we apply to every practice.</li>
      <li>Where studies were conducted by researchers affiliated with a practice, we disclose it — for Miracle of Mind and for Heartfulness alike, in identical wording.</li>
      <li>We never optimize a design or ranking decision to drive app installs. Success here is measured in trust and citation, not downloads.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <p>Our public proof lives in the project repository: a neutrality audit demonstrating that no practice-family bonus exists and that Miracle of Mind's page is no more favorably worded or placed than its peers', a per-page claims register, a decisions log, and a list of our lowest-confidence calls.</p>

  <h2>Funding</h2>
  <p>The registry is a non-commercial, volunteer project. It runs no advertising, accepts no payment for placement or ratings, and earns no commission from any practice's app or resource. Links to official free resources are provided identically for every practice as a convenience to readers.</p>

  <h2>Status</h2>
  <p>This is a staging preview. The site is intentionally not indexed by search engines, and its evidence claims await co-sign-off by a qualified medical or scientific reviewer before any public launch. If you are such a reviewer, or you spot an error, we want to hear about it.</p>

  <p class="disclaimer">Informational only — not medical advice, and not a substitute for professional care.</p>
</BaseLayout>
